1
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:13,767
You know that we have
different ways

2
00:00:13,833 --> 00:00:15,967
of disciplining our children.

3
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:18,333
What can we do?
She's the mother.

4
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:20,367
I can no longer tolerate
what you're doing.

5
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:21,833
So I'll get this.

6
00:00:21,900 --> 00:00:22,667
- Give that to me.
- It's mine now.

7
00:00:22,733 --> 00:00:24,200
Astrid!

8
00:00:24,267 --> 00:00:26,533
- Sorry.
- Emma isn't coming home.

9
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:29,933
What if she does something that
her employer doesn't like?

10
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,533
She'll get fired again!

11
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,567
This is the first time
I've seen Emma this happy,

12
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:35,100
and it's all
because she met Mookie.

13
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:36,467
Are you with someone?

14
00:00:39,333 --> 00:00:41,133
Can you not scare me like that?

15
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,833
Could this be what you heard?

16
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:45,233
I really hope she's asleep.

17
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:47,933
So I'll stay with you.

18
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:49,467
What's your secret?

19
00:00:49,533 --> 00:00:53,033
No one will help me
aside from myself.

20
00:00:53,100 --> 00:00:54,800
That's also what
I want you to learn.

21
00:00:54,867 --> 00:00:56,433
I want you to be brave.

22
00:01:31,433 --> 00:01:34,067
I want you to overcome
your fear.

23
00:01:34,133 --> 00:01:36,633
I want you to take care
of yourself.

24
00:01:39,867 --> 00:01:40,667
Mommy Emma...

25
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:45,967
I don't know how.

26
00:01:46,033 --> 00:01:48,033
I know...

27
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:50,167
it isn't easy.

28
00:01:50,233 --> 00:01:53,000
But that's the only way
I know I can help you,

29
00:01:53,067 --> 00:01:54,900
even if I'm not here.

30
00:01:54,967 --> 00:02:02,333
I'll be assured that you
can survive without me.

31
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:04,733
So, Dear...

32
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,900
promise me...

33
00:02:06,967 --> 00:02:10,467
you won't let your weakness
bring you down.

34
00:02:10,533 --> 00:02:13,067
Take care of yourself, okay?

35
00:02:14,833 --> 00:02:15,567
Yes, Mommy Emma.

36
00:02:16,700 --> 00:02:19,833
I'll be brave.

37
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:23,033
And whenever I'm discouraged...

38
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:26,233
I will think of you.

39
00:02:27,633 --> 00:02:30,667
Our memories together,

40
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:32,400
and...

41
00:02:32,467 --> 00:02:35,800
our bonding moments.

42
00:02:35,867 --> 00:02:40,167
And the memories that we
will create in the future.

43
00:02:43,467 --> 00:02:47,500
Mom, you're my source
of strength.

44
00:02:49,567 --> 00:02:52,067
I'll be brave for you.

45
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:54,433
Come here.

46
00:02:58,367 --> 00:03:00,433
Good night, Mommy Emma.

47
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:01,800
Good night, Dear.

48
00:03:28,567 --> 00:03:29,767
It's already morning.

49
00:03:30,833 --> 00:03:32,200
Mookie.

50
00:03:32,267 --> 00:03:33,533
Mookie.

51
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:34,533
Mookie.

52
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:36,567
I need to go.

53
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:39,067
Your mom might wake up any time.

54
00:03:39,133 --> 00:03:40,600
Wait.

55
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:09,167
Mookie.

56
00:04:09,233 --> 00:04:10,967
Can you read this?

57
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:16,433
I'm not sure if it's right.

58
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:24,933
Olive Caparas
shatters expectations

59
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:28,200
as she trades
her medical ambitions

60
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:32,267
for the reins
of Artemis Pharmacy.

61
00:04:32,333 --> 00:04:40,133
Notably, Olive Caparas, who
never secured a medical license.

62
00:04:42,633 --> 00:04:44,967
Never secured a medical license?

63
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:49,733
I'm not sure
if what I think is right.

64
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:56,133
That means mommy
isn't a real doctor.

65
00:04:57,767 --> 00:05:00,333
No. Maybe she studied medicine

66
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:03,867
but didn't finish school
and obtain a license.

67
00:05:03,967 --> 00:05:06,433
Why does she have to lie?

68
00:05:07,733 --> 00:05:10,967
I don't know. But I have to go.

69
00:05:11,033 --> 00:05:14,133
Don't worry,
I'll research about it.

70
00:05:18,533 --> 00:05:19,933
Be safe.

71
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:22,733
Mommy Emma...

72
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:27,600
Thank you.

73
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:33,800
Remember what I told you, okay?

74
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:36,633
Be brave. I'll be right back.

75
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:34,267
Emma, what are you doing here?

76
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:36,767
You don't have
a schedule here today.

77
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:38,333
I left something.

78
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,267
This.

79
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:40,867
I just came to get it.

80
00:06:40,967 --> 00:06:43,000
How did you get in?

81
00:06:43,067 --> 00:06:44,767
You swept the surroundings,
didn't you?

82
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:48,633
You left the gate open,
that's why, I got in.

83
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,467
Did I sweep? When...

84
00:06:50,533 --> 00:06:52,967
Flor, you forgot it already?

85
00:06:53,033 --> 00:06:55,333
You're becoming forgetful.

86
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:56,567
It's because you're swamped
with work.

87
00:06:56,633 --> 00:06:58,667
- I'll go ahead.
- Okay, okay.

88
00:06:58,733 --> 00:06:59,933
Dan might already
be waiting for me.

89
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:02,367
- Yes. Be safe.
- I will.

90
00:07:05,467 --> 00:07:07,100
Did I sweep earlier?

91
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:11,600
Oh, Emma.

92
00:07:11,667 --> 00:07:14,700
Make sure that
Ma'am Olive didn't see you.

93
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:17,433
You'd be dead meat if she did.

94
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:18,967
Don't do that again, Emma.

95
00:07:19,033 --> 00:07:20,700
I'm glad it happened.

96
00:07:20,767 --> 00:07:22,967
What's good about it?

97
00:07:23,033 --> 00:07:25,000
Are you really looking
for trouble?

98
00:07:25,067 --> 00:07:26,200
If that hadn't happened,

99
00:07:26,267 --> 00:07:28,633
I wouldn't have found out
about the rumor you heard,

100
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:31,900
that Ma'am Olive
is an unlicensed doctor.

101
00:07:31,967 --> 00:07:33,867
Who told you?

102
00:07:33,933 --> 00:07:36,000
We read it in a post
on the internet.

103
00:07:36,067 --> 00:07:39,233
She's not a licensed doctor.
She didn't finish medicine.

104
00:07:39,300 --> 00:07:44,167
Your accusation
will get us in trouble.

105
00:07:44,233 --> 00:07:47,233
Don't do anything,
even if it's true.

106
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:49,300
But she's the one acting
as Mookie's doctor.

107
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:52,633
Who knows, maybe she went back
to school and finished it.

108
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:55,867
Yes, Emma. For all you know,

109
00:07:55,933 --> 00:07:58,433
Ma'am Olive might have actually
finished her studies.

110
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,667
I hope you learned
your lesson, Mookie.

111
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,200
I'm getting tired
of disciplining you.

112
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:14,267
It's so hard to be your doctor.

113
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:24,300
Maybe the reason
you're struggling

114
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:27,033
because you're
not actually a doctor.

115
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,500
What did you say?

116
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:39,033
Do you really have
a doctor's license, Mommy?

117
00:08:41,767 --> 00:08:43,833
Are you really a doctor?

118
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:59,933
You're asking
if I have a license?

119
00:09:06,067 --> 00:09:07,833
Of course!

120
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:09,767
I have a medical license.

121
00:09:11,867 --> 00:09:13,033
But wait...

122
00:09:16,433 --> 00:09:18,567
why did you suddenly ask that?

123
00:09:20,733 --> 00:09:22,733
Did someone tell you about it?

124
00:09:26,433 --> 00:09:28,333
- No one.
- Is it you, Flor?

125
00:09:28,433 --> 00:09:31,533
Ma'am. No, it's not me, Ma'am.

126
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:34,400
I didn't tell her
you don't have a license.

127
00:09:34,467 --> 00:09:38,533
I even told Mookie that
you're the best doctor.

128
00:09:40,267 --> 00:09:41,967
So, if it's not you...

129
00:09:44,567 --> 00:09:45,700
then who is it?

130
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,533
Maybe it's from Ligaya.

131
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:53,033
Didn't she hear
the rumor in the hospital

132
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:55,867
that you're not a doctor?

133
00:09:55,933 --> 00:09:58,367
Even Emma knows it.

134
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:04,567
So, was it Emma who told Mookie?

135
00:10:04,667 --> 00:10:06,967
I'm not sure, Ma'am.

136
00:10:07,033 --> 00:10:08,333
I don't know.

137
00:10:11,267 --> 00:10:13,733
Next time, Mookie...

138
00:10:15,533 --> 00:10:19,400
don't believe any hearsay.

139
00:10:20,433 --> 00:10:22,333
Especially when it comes
from people

140
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:26,300
who treat gossip
as their main course.

141
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:29,033
Yes, Mommy.

142
00:10:30,367 --> 00:10:32,900
Are you done eating?

143
00:10:32,967 --> 00:10:34,033
If you are...

144
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:38,567
bring her to her room, Flor.

145
00:10:38,633 --> 00:10:39,967
Yes, Ma'am.

146
00:10:40,033 --> 00:10:41,067
Let's go.

147
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:17,233
Do you really have
a doctor's license, Mommy?

148
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:19,100
Are you really a doctor?

149
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:23,367
So, was it Emma who told Mookie?

150
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,133
That annoying Emma.

151
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:44,433
What a delightful surprise
to see you here, Astrid.

152
00:11:44,533 --> 00:11:48,100
You know I left a lot of work
behind when you sent me to Cebu.

153
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:52,833
Oh, dear Astrid.

154
00:11:56,967 --> 00:12:00,233
Do you already know what
the viral news is right now?

155
00:12:00,300 --> 00:12:01,800
News?

156
00:12:01,867 --> 00:12:03,067
What news?

157
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:05,733
Oh, Astrid dear.

158
00:12:07,933 --> 00:12:10,267
News flash.

159
00:12:11,467 --> 00:12:16,433
You are no longer the
retail operations manager

160
00:12:16,533 --> 00:12:18,300
of Artemis Pharmacy.

161
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:20,367
Olive?

162
00:12:21,567 --> 00:12:23,733
Yes, you heard me right.

163
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:27,900
- Olive...
- You are fired.

164
00:12:27,967 --> 00:12:30,833
Please, let's talk about it.

165
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:35,033
What I did before is for Mookie.

166
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:36,400
Oh, please.

167
00:12:38,033 --> 00:12:39,867
Spare me the drama.

168
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:42,500
Just leave.

169
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:45,600
Oh, by the way.

170
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:47,400
Don't forget to book a cab

171
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:50,433
because I'll get
your company car.

172
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:53,633
And on the way,

173
00:12:53,700 --> 00:12:56,567
you should also start looking
for another place to stay

174
00:12:56,633 --> 00:12:59,367
because you won't
be allowed to go back

175
00:12:59,433 --> 00:13:02,133
into the condominium
you're living in.

176
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:29,400
Hello, Virgie.

177
00:13:29,467 --> 00:13:31,233
How are you?

178
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:33,767
I know where Alice lives.

179
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,233
Really?

180
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:38,433
Please text me the address
right away, okay?

181
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:40,300
I'll go to them right now.

182
00:13:40,367 --> 00:13:43,000
- Okay.
- Okay.

183
00:13:43,067 --> 00:13:44,900
Ever since I lost them,

184
00:13:44,967 --> 00:13:47,800
it seems like something in me
has been missing.

185
00:13:47,867 --> 00:13:49,267
My being a mother.

186
00:13:49,333 --> 00:13:51,100
I don't feel whole.

187
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:55,167
There are a lot of things
I want to tell them.

188
00:13:55,267 --> 00:13:58,067
I did them wrong.

189
00:13:58,133 --> 00:14:03,267
I'm sure they'll get hurt
when they see me.

190
00:14:04,367 --> 00:14:07,667
But I hope they can forgive me.

191
00:14:07,733 --> 00:14:15,000
I can't do anything
at that time.

192
00:14:15,067 --> 00:14:20,967
All I know is that I did
what was best for them.

193
00:14:21,033 --> 00:14:22,567
What is their address?

194
00:14:22,633 --> 00:14:24,967
Where do they live?
Please give it to me.

195
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:05,900
Your mom said,
your child passed away?

196
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:09,700
Yes, Ma'am.

197
00:15:09,767 --> 00:15:12,167
Do you have other children?

198
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:13,767
No, Ma'am.

199
00:15:13,833 --> 00:15:17,000
And I can't bear
a child anymore.

200
00:15:17,067 --> 00:15:20,467
That's why you get
so excited for a child.

201
00:15:20,533 --> 00:15:22,433
Maybe that's why...

202
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:26,200
you were eager to talk
to Mookie before.

203
00:15:26,267 --> 00:15:28,967
That's why you kept on seeing
her in her room.

204
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,533
You're so pitiful...

205
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:38,833
you will forever long
for the love of a child.

206
00:15:38,933 --> 00:15:41,267
It really is a missed chance...

207
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:45,967
I will never know how it feels
like to be a mother.

208
00:15:46,033 --> 00:15:49,133
Because if I had the chance,

209
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:53,267
I will never hurt
nor lock my child in a room,

210
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:56,233
unlike other mothers out there.

211
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:05,100
Are you referring to me?

212
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:08,467
Sorry, Ma'am.

213
00:16:08,567 --> 00:16:11,267
But I saw you hurting Mookie.

214
00:16:11,333 --> 00:16:14,167
You were pulling out her hair
and slapping her.

215
00:16:16,033 --> 00:16:18,400
I'm sorry if you won't like
what I'm about to say,

216
00:16:18,467 --> 00:16:21,800
but the way you discipline
her is wrong.

217
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:27,800
Don't you dare lecture me
as if you know better.

218
00:16:27,867 --> 00:16:30,200
You didn't raise any child.

219
00:16:31,233 --> 00:16:36,367
The next time you interfere
with how I discipline my child,

220
00:16:36,433 --> 00:16:38,867
I won't just pour this on you.

221
00:16:38,933 --> 00:16:42,733
I'll make you drink
all this soapy water.

222
00:16:42,833 --> 00:16:44,467
Do you understand?

223
00:16:46,433 --> 00:16:48,867
Know your place.

224
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:28,533
Yes, Danilo.
Just pick me up later.

225
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:31,233
I still have a lot to do here.

226
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:33,800
Why do you sound sad?

227
00:17:33,867 --> 00:17:34,933
Did something happen?

228
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,000
No, nothing.

229
00:17:36,067 --> 00:17:37,367
I have to go. I still have a lot
of laundry to do.

230
00:17:37,433 --> 00:17:39,100
Just pick me up later, okay?

231
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:28,500
Emma, please take care of this.

232
00:18:32,733 --> 00:18:34,567
- Flor.
- Yes, Ma'am.

233
00:18:34,633 --> 00:18:37,633
- My bag and my keys.
- Okay, wait, Ma'am.

234
00:19:06,767 --> 00:19:08,667
Ever since they
were separated from me,

235
00:19:08,733 --> 00:19:11,667
it's like there is a missing
piece in my wholebeing.

236
00:19:11,733 --> 00:19:14,800
My motherhood is not complete.

237
00:19:16,367 --> 00:19:19,033
I have so much to say to them.

238
00:19:19,100 --> 00:19:21,833
I caused them too much trouble.

239
00:19:21,900 --> 00:19:25,000
I'm sure if they saw me...

240
00:19:25,067 --> 00:19:27,933
they'll get hurt.

241
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:31,600
But I hope that if they see me,
they can forgive me.

242
00:19:32,733 --> 00:19:36,333
I'll be home late,
I have a lot to do at work.

243
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:38,433
- You take charge here.
- Okay, Ma'am.

244
00:20:09,067 --> 00:20:10,200
Ma'am Alice...

245
00:20:14,767 --> 00:20:16,567
I'm Ligaya.

246
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:25,700
Emma, Ma'am Olive just left,
take care of this please,

247
00:20:25,767 --> 00:20:27,400
I'll go inside first,
please work on this.

248
00:20:27,467 --> 00:20:31,000
Wait, maybe you can take
Mookie out for a while.

249
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:33,567
Oh no, Emma. Here you go again.

250
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:37,167
You're asking for trouble
then you'll drag me into this.

251
00:20:37,267 --> 00:20:40,600
Please, even for a short time,
I feel bad for the kid.

252
00:20:44,167 --> 00:20:47,800
Ma'am Alice, thank you
that I saw you again,

253
00:20:47,867 --> 00:20:50,567
I've been searching for you
for a long time now.

254
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:55,300
How are my children?

255
00:20:55,367 --> 00:20:58,233
I just want to see them.

256
00:20:58,300 --> 00:21:01,133
Your children are not with me.

257
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:06,833
Ma'am Alice, aren't they not...

258
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:09,833
I gave my children to you,

259
00:21:09,933 --> 00:21:11,933
I just want to ask
how they're doing,

260
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:14,733
I just want to see the two kids.

261
00:21:22,867 --> 00:21:25,833
There, go for it.

262
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:27,133
Just a little bit more.

263
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:30,467
A little bit more, Mookie.

264
00:21:30,533 --> 00:21:32,267
Mommy Emma, please just
stay there.

265
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:35,067
I'm so happy,
you can now take a step.

266
00:21:35,133 --> 00:21:37,133
I know right, Mommy Emma.

267
00:21:39,067 --> 00:21:42,867
But Mommy Emma,
why is it like this...

268
00:21:42,967 --> 00:21:47,633
my mom hasn't been giving me
canixidol lately,

269
00:21:47,700 --> 00:21:49,367
but why is it like this...

270
00:21:49,433 --> 00:21:52,367
when she did not give me
canixidol, I can walk.

271
00:21:52,433 --> 00:21:54,467
Mookie, I also don't know.

272
00:21:57,233 --> 00:22:01,000
Don't think about it,
take a seat first.

273
00:22:01,067 --> 00:22:02,233
There.

274
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:11,967
Mommy Emma...

275
00:22:12,033 --> 00:22:15,733
maybe the article
is saying the truth...

276
00:22:17,367 --> 00:22:20,667
that my mom is not
really a doctor.

277
00:22:24,067 --> 00:22:26,667
Don't think about it, okay?

278
00:22:26,733 --> 00:22:29,767
If you want,
we can practice again.

279
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:31,333
But...

280
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:34,300
I won't hold you, okay?
But I'll assist in your walking.

281
00:22:34,367 --> 00:22:36,300
Are you sure, Mommy Emma?

282
00:22:36,367 --> 00:22:37,833
- I might fall.
- You can do it.

283
00:22:37,900 --> 00:22:41,267
No, I'm here for you.
Do you want to try it?

284
00:22:41,333 --> 00:22:42,300
I'll just help you stand.

285
00:22:43,333 --> 00:22:44,833
Thanks, Mommy Emma.

286
00:22:44,900 --> 00:22:47,300
Try it on your own first, okay?
I'll be here.

287
00:22:49,267 --> 00:22:52,033
Don't rush it, okay?
Just take it slow.

288
00:22:59,300 --> 00:23:02,167
Ma'am, please I'm begging you.

289
00:23:02,233 --> 00:23:05,900
Even just for a bit,
I just want to look at them.

290
00:23:08,567 --> 00:23:12,733
I won't talk to them.
I just want to see them.

291
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:17,767
That's the thing,
your children are not with me.

292
00:23:17,833 --> 00:23:23,533
What do you mean? Do they have
their own families now?

293
00:23:23,633 --> 00:23:26,300
They did not grow up in my care.

294
00:23:28,567 --> 00:23:29,767
You can do it.

295
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,433
Do really have
a doctor's license?

296
00:23:42,500 --> 00:23:44,467
The way you're trying
to dicipline her is wrong.

297
00:23:44,533 --> 00:23:47,333
Are you really a doctor?

298
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:48,700
Snake.

299
00:23:50,133 --> 00:23:52,200
Oh, you're doing it, Mookie.

300
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:57,600
I'm just here, okay?

301
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:09,500
The next time
that you'll lie to me,

302
00:24:09,567 --> 00:24:11,900
there will be consequences.

303
00:24:11,967 --> 00:24:14,800
You are no different
from Ma'am Olive.

304
00:24:14,867 --> 00:24:17,233
You are a useless mother.

305
00:24:17,300 --> 00:24:21,267
It's not enough that I kick Emma
out and hurt her.

306
00:24:21,333 --> 00:24:22,700
What do you mean?

307
00:24:22,767 --> 00:24:24,600
You called for me?

308
00:24:24,667 --> 00:24:28,400
The storage room is dirty,
can you clean it?

309
00:24:29,833 --> 00:24:32,133
Where is my necklace?

310
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:33,467
Why is this here?

311
00:24:33,533 --> 00:24:36,533
Sir, arrest her. She stole
from us the other night,

312
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:40,300
and now, caught in the act,
she's stealing again.
